title: The iPhone is switching cables again. This time, that’s good.
description: No, Apple’s big connector plug switch to USB-C isn’t (just) a scam to sell more chargers.

title: Musk may have violated FTC privacy order, new court filing shows
description: Elon Musk repeatedly made business decisions after his takeover of Twitter last year that violated the company’s internal policies, a new court filing alleges.

title: Apple event live updates: Get the latest iPhone, Apple Watch news
description: The September Apple event is set to announce the latest on the iPhone 15 and Apple Watch series. Follow along for the latest updates and announcements live.

title: Kim and Putin may meet at this spaceport in Russian far east. Why there?
description: The Vostochny Cosmodrome is the country’s main spaceport. The setting could provide a powerful symbol if Kim Jong Un and Vladimir Putin meet there.

title: This planet light-years from Earth may be covered in ocean, NASA says
description: NASA says exoplanet K2-18 b could be a “Hycean” planet, as the Webb telescope helped detect methane and carbon dioxide there, though it is unclear if it could support life.

title: Google trial set to begin in first major tech antitrust case in decades
description: Not since the U.S. government tried to break up Microsoft in 2000 has the federal government taken on a major tech giant over its business practice.

title: Nvidia, Palantir and more companies join White House AI pledge
description: The commitments include a promise to develop technology to identify AI-generated images and a vow to share data about safety with the government and academics.
